# Playground Media Dimensions

When adding or modifying `<img>` or `<video>` elements inside `.playground-media` in the playground page, always include `width` and `height` attributes with the actual pixel dimensions of the media file.

## Why

The masonry grid uses these attributes to reserve the correct space before media loads, preventing layout shift. Without them, cards collapse to 0 height until media loads.

## How

1. Check dimensions: `sips -g pixelWidth -g pixelHeight <file>` for images, `ffprobe -v error -select_streams v:0 -show_entries stream=width,height -of csv=s=x:p=0 <file>` for videos.
2. Add the attributes to the element.

```html
<!-- Images -->
<img src="/images/playground/example.png" alt="..." width="1024" height="548">

<!-- Videos -->
<video class="playground-video" muted autoplay loop playsinline preload="metadata" src="/video/example.mp4" width="1920" height="1080"></video>
```
